data.content:
`[ExpectedException]` was removed in MSTest v4. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Similarly for your second test:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => Process());
}
```

For **async** methods, use `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(...)`. If you used `AllowDerivedTypes = true`, use `Assert.Throws<T>` instead (matches derived types too).

> **Tip:** On v3 the analyzer `MSTEST0006` flags `[ExpectedException]` usage, so you can migrate before upgrading.

